        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-17 11:48:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\nHi,\n\nCould you please look at these changes? This is my first contribution using Gerrit, and I just want to make sure I have not done anything wrong.\n\nAlso, unfortunately, resolving this issue required a quiet amount of refactoring with significant updates (I had around 30 commits initially that I have grouped in 7 to reflect the intent of each set of modifications). I hope that is alright.\n\nThank you in advance for your help and mentoring.",
        "patchset_number": 10
      },
      {
        "id": "7cdbb61b90a3f7b39ef3f6bb29cf953c063a618c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6614,
          "name": "Francis Toth",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "francis.toth@yoppworks.com",
          "username": "francistoth"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-17 12:05:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\nHi,\n\nCould you please review these changes? They refer to SDC-2499, which fixes many of the problems related to the testing of asdctool. It is part of a topic which goal is to separate the report writing and formatting logic to improve maintainability and testability. In this change, we only focus on eliminating any global mutable static state residing in ValidationConfig Manager.\n\nThank you in advance for your help.\n\nFrancis.",
        "patchset_number": 10
      },
      {
        "id": "7398046f927d71eada0ba8aa12b7519b4b534859",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6597,
